qas.question: France rose to power after what war?
What empire declined after the Crimean War?
The Crimean war marked the end of what dominant European power?

context: <a0_0>The Crimean War<a0_0/> marked the ascendancy of France to the position of pre-eminent power on the Continent,:411 the continued decline of <a1_0>the Ottoman Empire<a1_0/>, and the beginning of a decline for Tsarist Russia. As Fuller notes, "Russia had been beaten on the Crimean peninsula, and the military feared that it would inevitably be beaten again unless steps were taken to surmount its military weakness." The Crimean War marks the demise of the <a2_0>Concert of Europe<a2_0/>, the balance of power that had dominated Europe since the Congress of Vienna in 1815, and which had included France, Russia, Austria and the United Kingdom.
